<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,799,1221]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Remarks: In the redescription of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Gerecke (2014 b)" authorityName=", Gerecke" authorityYear="2014" box="[576,927,835,862]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipes">
<emphasis box="[576,721,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. gracilipes</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[736,927,835,862]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="735 - 759" refId="ref74426" refString="Gerecke, R. (2014 b) The water mites of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari, Hydrachnidia: Hygrobatidae) in Corsica and Sardinia. Zoosystema, 36 (4), 735 - 759. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2014 n 4 a 3" type="journal article" year="2014">Gerecke (2014b)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not mention its similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke &amp; Di Sabatino" authorityYear="2013" box="[1305,1429,835,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giustinii">
<emphasis box="[1305,1429,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. giustinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Common features are the excretory pore with ring-shaped sclerotization, fusion of Vgl-1+2, convex anterior margin of male genital plate, and a slightly enlarged I-L-5. In addition to a distinct difference in size – both sexes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke &amp; Di Sabatino" authorityYear="2013" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giustinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. giustinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are minor in nearly all measurements – the two species differ as follows (
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gerecke" authorityYear="2014" box="[1103,1248,943,969]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipes">
<emphasis box="[1103,1248,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. gracilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in parentheses): 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke &amp; Di Sabatino" authorityYear="2013" box="[151,366,979,1005]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giustinii">
<emphasis box="[151,366,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Atractides giustinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has relatively shorter palp segments P-3 and P-4 - relative L 24-25 (26), resp. 32-33 (38) %, P- 2/P-4 ratio&gt; 0.6 (&lt;0.6); a slenderer P-3, with L/H 
<specimenCount box="[723,765,1015,1041]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
&gt; 1.8 (&lt;1.8), 
<specimenCount box="[926,968,1015,1041]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
&gt; 2.2 (&lt;2.1), a stouter P-4, with L/H 
<specimenCount box="[1394,1436,1015,1041]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
&lt;3.2 (&gt; 3.4), 
<specimenCount box="[305,347,1051,1077]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="female">♀♀</specimenCount>
&lt;4.0 (&gt; 4.5). Clear differences are found also in proportions of the first leg: ventral margin I-L-5 relatively shortened, I-L-5 dL/vL ratio&gt; 1.4 (&lt;1.4); S-1/-2 distance 
<specimenCount box="[918,960,1087,1113]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="male">♂♂</specimenCount>
&gt; 20 (15), 
<specimenCount box="[1085,1106,1087,1113]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
&gt; 35 (25), both setae shorter; I-L- 
<quantity box="[197,239,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
the centre not as strongly narrowed as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gerecke" authorityYear="2014" box="[706,849,1123,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipes">
<emphasis box="[706,849,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. gracilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
